4.4.20 Modify BST to add a method remove() that takes a Key argument and
removes that key (and the corresponding value) from the symbol table, if it exists.
Hint : Replace the key (and its associated value) with the next largest key in the BST
(and its associated value); then remove from the BST the node that contained the
next largest key

    public void remove(Key key)
    {
        Node prv = root;
        Node curr = root;
        while (curr != null) {
            int cmp = key.compareTo(curr.key);
            if (cmp < 0) { // key < curr
                prv =  curr;
                curr = curr.left;
            }
            else if (cmp > 0) {
                prv =  curr;
                curr = curr.right;
            }
            // found item to rmv
            else {
                Node lft = curr.left;
                Node rt = curr.right;
                // if item to rmv is a leaf
                if (lft == null && rt == null) {
                    curr = null;
                    return;
                }
                // if item to rmv has right child, link item's parent to
                // the child
                else if (lft == null){
                    prv.right = rt;
                    curr = null;
                    return;
                }
                else {
                    prv.left = lft;
                    curr = null;
                    return;
                }
            }
        }
    }
